---
// About page — Cotton background, Noir text
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/navigation/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/navigation/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="About"
  description="Ncheta Magazine — documenting African art narratives, from historical scholarship to the contemporary market."
>
  <Header />
  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
    <!-- Breadcrumb -->
    <nav
      class="mb-8 font-inter text-xs text-noir/40 flex gap-2"
      aria-label="Breadcrumb"
    >
      <a href="/" class="transition-colors">Home</a>
      <span>/</span>
      <span class="text-noir/60">About</span>
    </nav>

    <h1 class="font-cinzel font-bold text-4xl md:text-5xl text-noir mb-3">
      About Ncheta
    </h1>
    <p
      class="font-inter text-base text-noir/50 mb-10 border-l-2 border-maroon pl-4"
    >
      "Ncheta" means <em>remember</em> in Igbo — and that is our mission.
    </p>

    <div class="prose-content">
      <p>
        Ncheta magazine is a record of West African art curated by the people
        who live in it.
      </p>
      <p>
        Ncheta: <em>to remember</em>, originates from the Igbo language. This
        editorial intends to make the documentation of West African art a
        standard practice across the region.
      </p>
      <p>
        Our stories are written by people who interact with the art ecosystem
        first hand: artists, academics, curators, critics, gallerists,
        publicists and collectors.
      </p>
      <p>
        Reportage at Ncheta Magazine spans across <strong>all</strong> countries within
        the West African region. Our readership is not paywalled and our editorial
        is independent.
      </p>
      <p>
        We offer artists, galleries and institutions media representation
        services customised to suit their needs.
      </p>
      <p>
        We curate the content we publish in accordance with our resolve to
        present art from West Africa, recorded for now and the future.
      </p>
      <h2>Get in Touch</h2>
      <p>
        Email <a href="mailto:hello@nchetamagazine.com"
          >hello@nchetamagazine.com</a
        > to discuss rates, lead times, and available placements, or visit our&nbsp;
        <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
